         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Georgetown ¶ Sept 10th 1885 ¶ Baron Von Müller ¶ Dear Sir ¶  ¶ I hereby forward you under seprate cover, a herb, also a piece of the same made up into a compound. The Compound — (which I believe is ma...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">85.09.10</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Nicholas Samwell</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Blumea axillaris</seg> (MEL 545065). MS annotation by M: 'Answ 16/10/85 FvM'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Georgetown<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by M: 'Queensland'.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Sept 10th 1885</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Von Müller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hereby forward you under seprate cover, a herb, also a piece of the same made up into a compound. The Compound — (which I believe is made from this herb) is used by the Chineese at Gilberton<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Qld.</p>
               </note> for curing snake bites, for which purpose I have seen it used with good results the compound was pounded, and mixed with brandy, and then given internally, wound scarified &amp; washed with water, then the same mixture applied — I have seen a horse bitten by a black Snake cured in this manner. I have also seen the wounds on two Chinamen who were bitten by a tiger Snake who said they were cured in this manner.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If the herb is so — it might become of some good — The herb might be a very common one for all I know, for "I am not much of a herbist". However if you should discover anything you could kindly let me know the name of the herb etc.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hopeing that you receive it safetly and can make something out of it, also that it is not to scarious. I remain —</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours Very Truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>N. Samwell</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Address —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">N. Samwell</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Georgetown, Etheridge Gold Field</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">North Queensland</p>
